'''Eric Anders Smith''' (born 8 January 1997) is a Swedish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[central defender]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[FC St. Pauli]] and the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Eric Smith|url=https://svenskfotboll.se/allsvenskan/person/?playerid=8057|publisher=Svenskfotboll|access-date=8 September 2014}}</ref>

==Club career==
In January 2016, Smith joined Swedish team [[IFK Norrköping]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Eric Smith|url=http://www.folkbladet.se/sport/visst-var-det-smith-9058215.aspx|publisher=folkbladet|access-date=20 January 2016}}</ref> and moved abroad in June 2018 signing with [[K.A.A. Gent|Gent]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Welkom Eric Smith!|url=https://www.kaagent.be/nl/supporter/news/20-06-2018/welkom-eric-smith|publisher=K.A.A. Gent|access-date=27 July 2018}}</ref>

Smith joined [[2. Bundesliga]] club [[FC St. Pauli]] on loan for the second half of the [[2020–21 2. Bundesliga|2020–21 season]]. FC St. Pauli secured an option to sign him permanently.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mit Kaufoption: Der FC St. Pauli leiht Eric Smith von KAA Gent aus |url=https://www.kicker.de/mit-kaufoption-st-pauli-leiht-gents-smith-aus-794024/artikel |website=kicker |access-date=7 January 2021 |language=de |date=7 January 2021}}</ref>

== International career ==
On 12 May 2026, Smith was named in the Sweden squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-12 |title=Mystiskt inlägg efter petningen |url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/landslaget/har-ar-sveriges-trupp-till-fotbolls-vm-2026/ |access-date=2026-05-15 |website=www.expressen.se |language=sv}}</ref> Smith made his full international debut on 1 June 2026 in a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] 1–3 loss against [[Norway national football team|Norway]], playing for 45 minutes as a centre-back before being replaced by [[Alexander Bernhardsson]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Sweden vs. Norway |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/matchfakta/norge-sverige-landskamper-herr-senior/6707826/ |website=SvFF}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Smith was born in Sweden, and his father [[Anders Smith|Anders]] is a former footballer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sverigesradio.se/sida/artikel.aspx?programid=128&artikel=6131119|title=Eric Smith: "Jag tänker alltid på fotbollen" - P4 Halland|publisher=Sveriges Radio|language=sv}}</ref>

